goals.question: What is the correlation between u and v?

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.scatter(data['u'], data['v'])
    plt.xlabel('u')
    plt.ylabel('v')
    plt.title('What is the correlation between u and v?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.hist(data['u'], bins=30, color='blue', alpha=0.7, label='u')
    plt.axvline(data['u'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=2, label=f"Mean: {data['u'].mean():.2f}")
    plt.xlabel('u')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of u?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.hist(data['v'], bins=30, color='blue', alpha=0.7, label='v')
    plt.axvline(data['v'].median(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=2, label=f"Median: {data['v'].median():.2f}")
    plt.xlabel('v')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of v?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
import numpy as np

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    hb = ax.hist2d(data['u'], data['v'], bins=50, cmap='viridis')
    ax.set_xlabel('u')
    ax.set_ylabel('v')
    plt.colorbar(hb[3], ax=ax)
    plt.title('What is the joint distribution of u and v?')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    data.boxplot(column=['u', 'v'], ax=ax)
    plt.title("What is the mean and standard deviation of u and v?", wrap=True)
    plt.legend(['u', 'v'], loc='upper right')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
